cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.SE, cs.DC 

The paper deals with authenticated data storage on an untrusted platform, which is a security issue and falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The proposed solution is a key-value store, which involves data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also mentions LevelDB and RocksDB, which are database systems (cs.DB). The use of Intel SGX enclaves involves system-level programming and hardware architecture (cs.SE). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed solution, which involves performance analysis and evaluation (cs.DC).
